sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as spark-operator-webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as spark-operator-controller
    participant SparkSubmit as spark-submit<br/>(local exec)
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP
    participant Executors as Spark Executor Pods<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP
    participant SparkUI as Spark UI Service<br/>4040/TCP HTTP
    participant SparkConnect as SparkConnect Server<br/>15002/TCP gRPC
    participant Workbench as ODH/RHOAI Workbench

    Note over User, Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443, User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Admission Review (mutate + validate)<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS 1.2+ (self-signed)<br/>API Server cert
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Lookup SparkApplication spec<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (defaults set, validated)
    K8sAPI-->>User: SparkApplication created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch detects new SparkApplication<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>SparkSubmit: Execute spark-submit<br/>Local process (no network)
    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: Create Driver Pod<br/>HTTPS/443

    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Pod Admission Review (mutate)<br/>HTTPS/9443
    Note over Webhook: 22 sequential mutation steps:<br/>volumes, env vars, sidecars,<br/>GPU, monitoring, scheduler, etc.
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod spec

    Driver->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Pod Admission Review (mutate)<br/>HTTPS/9443
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod spec

    Driver->>Executors: RPC communication<br/>TCP/7078 (driver-rpc)<br/>TCP/7079 (block manager)<br/>No encryption

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Spark UI Service<br/>HTTPS/443
    User->>SparkUI: View Spark UI<br/>HTTP/4040, No auth

    Executors-->>Driver: Task results
    Driver-->>Controller: Application completes
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update SparkApplication status<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over User, Workbench: Flow 2: SparkConnect Session

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply SparkConnect CR<br/>HTTPS/443, User credentials
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch detects SparkConnect CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create SparkConnect Server + Service<br/>HTTPS/443

    Workbench->>SparkConnect: Interactive Spark session<br/>gRPC/15002, No encryption, No auth
    SparkConnect->>Executors: Executor management<br/>TCP/7078, 7079

    Note over Webhook, K8sAPI: Flow 3: Webhook Certificate Rotation

    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Write self-signed cert to Secret<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Update MutatingWebhookConfiguration<br/>caBundle injection, HTTPS/443
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Update ValidatingWebhookConfiguration<br/>caBundle injection, HTTPS/443
